        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What Executives Need from GenAI FinOps"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "CFOs and VPs ask four questions about GenAI spend: Are we on budget? Is the spend generating margin? Which teams or features are driving cost growth? And what risks need action this month? An executive dashboard answers all four at a glance \u2014 without requiring the viewer to understand tokens, rate cards, or chargeback mechanics. The design principle is: one page, four KPIs, three supporting charts, and a prioritised alert list."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Executive dashboard mockup"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Executive Summary Metrics Model"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The executive layer aggregates the detailed FinOps metrics into five headline numbers: total spend, budget utilization, gross margin, cost per conversation, and alert count. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "headline"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " property generates a one-sentence narrative automatically \u2014 useful for weekly digest emails and Slack updates."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom datetime import date\nfrom typing import Optional\n\n@dataclass\nclass ExecSummaryMetrics:\n    period: str\n    total_spend_usd: float\n    budget_usd: float\n    gross_margin_pct: float\n    avg_cost_per_conv_usd: float\n    active_alerts_critical: int\n    active_alerts_warn: int\n    top_team: str\n    top_team_spend_usd: float\n    mom_change_pct: float    # month-over-month change in total spend\n\n    @property\n    def budget_utilization_pct(self) -> float:\n        return self.total_spend_usd / self.budget_usd * 100 if self.budget_usd else 0.0\n\n    @property\n    def budget_status(self) -> str:\n        u = self.budget_utilization_pct\n        if u >= 100:\n            return \"OVER_BUDGET\"\n        if u >= 90:\n            return \"AT_RISK\"\n        if u >= 75:\n            return \"ON_TRACK\"\n        return \"UNDER_BUDGET\"\n\n    @property\n    def headline(self) -> str:\n        \"\"\"One-sentence executive summary.\"\"\"\"\n        budget_word = {\n            \"OVER_BUDGET\": \"exceeded budget\",\n            \"AT_RISK\": \"is at risk of exceeding budget\",\n            \"ON_TRACK\": \"is on track\",\n            \"UNDER_BUDGET\": \"is under budget\",\n        }[self.budget_status]\n        return (\n            f\"GenAI spend for {self.period} is ${self.total_spend_usd/1000:.0f}K \"\n            f\"({self.budget_utilization_pct:.0f}% of ${self.budget_usd/1000:.0f}K budget) \u2014 \"\n            f\"{budget_word}. Gross margin: {self.gross_margin_pct:.1f}%.\"\n        )"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Building the Summary from the Data Warehouse"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The executive summary pulls from the same "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "conversation_costs"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " table used throughout the FinOps pipeline. It adds three cross-cuts: total spend vs budget, alert counts from the monitoring layer, and a month-over-month delta computed by joining to the prior period."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import sqlite3\nfrom datetime import date\n\ndef build_exec_summary(\n    db: sqlite3.Connection,\n    period: str,\n    budget_usd: float,\n) -> ExecSummaryMetrics:\n    spend_row = db.execute(\"\"\"        SELECT\n            SUM(total_cost_usd)    AS total_spend,\n            COUNT(DISTINCT team)   AS n_teams\n        FROM conversation_costs\n        WHERE period = ?\n    \"\"\", (period,)).fetchone()\n\n    top_team_row = db.execute(\"\"\"        SELECT team, SUM(total_cost_usd) AS spend\n        FROM conversation_costs\n        WHERE period = ?\n        GROUP BY team\n        ORDER BY spend DESC\n        LIMIT 1\n    \"\"\", (period,)).fetchone()\n\n    alert_row = db.execute(\"\"\"        SELECT\n            SUM(CASE WHEN severity = 'CRITICAL' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS critical,\n            SUM(CASE WHEN severity = 'WARN'     THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS warn\n        FROM metric_alerts\n        WHERE period = ? AND resolved = 0\n    \"\"\", (period,)).fetchone()\n\n    # Prior month for MoM\n    prior_period = _prior_month(period)\n    prior_spend = db.execute(\n        \"SELECT SUM(total_cost_usd) FROM conversation_costs WHERE period = ?\",\n        (prior_period,)\n    ).fetchone()[0] or 0.0\n\n    total = spend_row[\"total_spend\"] or 0.0\n    mom = (total - prior_spend) / prior_spend if prior_spend else 0.0\n\n    return ExecSummaryMetrics(\n        period=period,\n        total_spend_usd=total,\n        budget_usd=budget_usd,\n        gross_margin_pct=0.0,      # populated separately from margin report\n        avg_cost_per_conv_usd=0.0, # populated separately from unit metrics\n        active_alerts_critical=alert_row[\"critical\"] or 0,\n        active_alerts_warn=alert_row[\"warn\"] or 0,\n        top_team=top_team_row[\"team\"] if top_team_row else \"\u2014\",\n        top_team_spend_usd=top_team_row[\"spend\"] if top_team_row else 0.0,\n        mom_change_pct=mom,\n    )\n\ndef _prior_month(period: str) -> str:\n    y, m = int(period[:4]), int(period[5:7])\n    m -= 1\n    if m == 0:\n        m, y = 12, y - 1\n    return f\"{y}-{m:02d}\""
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Compute prior-month comparisons by shifting the YYYY-MM string, not by subtracting 30 days from today. "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "code"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "today - 30 days"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " will cross month boundaries inconsistently (e.g. March 1 \u2212 30d = Jan 30, skipping February entirely)."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
