      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Monthly Board Pack Generation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For monthly business reviews and board packs, the dashboard data is rendered into narrative slides. Each slide has a title, a 2\u20133 sentence written commentary (suitable for a CFO who will not click through to raw data), and a chart reference. The narrative is generated from the metrics, not written by hand."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\n\n@dataclass\nclass BoardPackSlide:\n    title: str\n    narrative: str     # 2\u20133 sentence written commentary for CFO\n    metrics: dict[str, str]   # label -> formatted value\n    chart_ref: str     # reference to pre-built chart image or data\n\ndef build_monthly_board_pack(\n    summary: ExecSummaryMetrics,\n    margin_by_feature: dict[str, float],\n    alerts: list,\n    top_movers: list[dict],\n) -> list[BoardPackSlide]:\n    slides = []\n\n    # Slide 1: Executive summary\n    alerts_note = (\n        f\"{summary.active_alerts_critical} critical and {summary.active_alerts_warn} warning alerts active.\"\n        if summary.active_alerts_critical or summary.active_alerts_warn\n        else \"No critical alerts this period.\"\n    )\n    slides.append(BoardPackSlide(\n        title=\"GenAI Spend \u2014 Executive Summary\",\n        narrative=(\n            f\"{summary.headline} \"\n            f\"Month-over-month change: {summary.mom_change_pct:+.1%}. \"\n            f\"{alerts_note}\"\n        ),\n        metrics={\n            \"Total Spend (MTD)\":      f\"${summary.total_spend_usd:,.0f}\",\n            \"Budget\":                  f\"${summary.budget_usd:,.0f}\",\n            \"Budget Utilization\":      f\"{summary.budget_utilization_pct:.1f}%\",\n            \"Portfolio Gross Margin\":  f\"{summary.gross_margin_pct:.1f}%\",\n            \"Avg Cost / Conversation\": f\"${summary.avg_cost_per_conv_usd:.4f}\",\n        },\n        chart_ref=\"spend_trend_6mo\",\n    ))\n\n    # Slide 2: Feature margin health\n    margin_notes = \", \".join(\n        f\"{feat}: {gm:.0f}%\" for feat, gm in sorted(margin_by_feature.items(), key=lambda x: x[1])\n    )\n    slides.append(BoardPackSlide(\n        title=\"Feature-Level Gross Margin\",\n        narrative=(\n            f\"Gross margin by feature ranges from \"\n            f\"{min(margin_by_feature.values()):.0f}% to {max(margin_by_feature.values()):.0f}%. \"\n            f\"Features below 50% target: \"\n            f\"{sum(1 for v in margin_by_feature.values() if v < 50)}. \"\n            f\"Breakdown: {margin_notes}.\"\n        ),\n        metrics={feat: f\"{gm:.1f}%\" for feat, gm in margin_by_feature.items()},\n        chart_ref=\"margin_by_feature_bar\",\n    ))\n\n    # Slide 3: Top movers\n    mover_narrative = \"; \".join(\n        f\"{m['team']}/{m['feature']}: {m['delta_pct']:+.0%} (${m['delta_usd']:+,.0f})\"\n        for m in top_movers[:3]\n    )\n    slides.append(BoardPackSlide(\n        title=\"Top Cost Movers Month-over-Month\",\n        narrative=(\n            f\"Largest cost changes vs prior month: {mover_narrative}. \"\n            f\"Investigations are in progress for movements exceeding 20%.\"\n        ),\n        metrics={f\"{m['team']}/{m['feature']}\": f\"{m['delta_pct']:+.1%}\" for m in top_movers},\n        chart_ref=\"top_movers_waterfall\",\n    ))\n\n    return slides"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Dashboard Cache and Refresh"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Executive dashboards must load instantly. Querying the data warehouse at page-load time introduces 3\u201315 second latency that executives will not tolerate. Materialise the dashboard payload to a JSON file on a scheduled refresh (hourly during business hours, daily overnight). The web layer reads the file."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import sqlite3\nfrom datetime import date, datetime\nimport json\n\ndef refresh_exec_dashboard_cache(\n    db: sqlite3.Connection,\n    period: str,\n    budget_usd: float,\n    output_path: str,\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Materialise all dashboard data to a JSON file.\n    The web dashboard reads this file \u2014 decoupling the DB query latency\n    from the dashboard page load time.\n    \"\"\"\"\n    summary = build_exec_summary(db, period, budget_usd)\n\n    payload = {\n        \"generated_at\": datetime.utcnow().isoformat(),\n        \"period\": period,\n        \"headline\": summary.headline,\n        \"kpis\": {\n            \"total_spend_usd\":       summary.total_spend_usd,\n            \"budget_usd\":             summary.budget_usd,\n            \"budget_utilization_pct\": summary.budget_utilization_pct,\n            \"gross_margin_pct\":       summary.gross_margin_pct,\n            \"avg_cost_per_conv_usd\":  summary.avg_cost_per_conv_usd,\n            \"mom_change_pct\":         summary.mom_change_pct,\n            \"alerts_critical\":        summary.active_alerts_critical,\n            \"alerts_warn\":            summary.active_alerts_warn,\n        },\n        \"budget_status\": summary.budget_status,\n    }\n    with open(output_path, \"w\") as f:\n        json.dump(payload, f, indent=2)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Design Principles for Executive Dashboards"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "No jargon"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": 'Cost per conversation' is acceptable; 'P95 token-weighted blended rate' is not. Map technical metrics to business language before displaying."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Status first, data second"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": Show GREEN/YELLOW/RED status on every KPI tile. Executives scan for red before reading numbers."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "One click to the cause"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": Every alert and top-mover entry should link directly to the relevant drill-down (team dashboard, feature margin report, anomaly detail)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Stable layout"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": Do not change the tile positions, axis scales, or colour coding between months. Executives build muscle memory for where to look."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Written narrative alongside charts"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": Charts require interpretation. A two-sentence narrative ('Spend is 92% of budget with 8 days left \u2014 on track') prevents misreading."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Alerting into the Executive Layer"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Not every FinOps alert belongs in the executive view. Filter to three categories: budget breaches (spend > 100% of monthly allocation), gross margin degradation (GM drops > 5pp in a single month), and critical unit economics (P95 cost/conv exceeds 5\u00d7 target). All other alerts stay in the operational layer."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "table",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableHeader",
                "attrs": {},
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Alert Type"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableHeader",
                "attrs": {},
